Homework 3¶

I used model and dataset I trained for Homework 2, but instead of Logistic Regression I used AdaBoostClassifier. I sampled 3 observations and generated 3 explanations for different seeds. The explanations seems reasonable and consistent for different seeds.

Education, age and relationship status seem to play important role in all predctions - people with higher education, older nad in relationship are more prone to be predicted with high income.

def load_adult_dataset():
    data = pd.read_csv('adult.csv').dropna()
    education_levels = {
    "Preschool": 1,
    "1st-4th": 2,
    "5th-6th": 3,
    "7th-8th": 4,
    "9th": 5,
    "10th": 6,
    "11th": 7,
    "12th": 8,
    "Some-college": 9,
    "HS-grad": 10,
    "Assoc-acdm": 11,
    "Assoc-voc": 12,
    "Bachelors": 13,
    "Masters": 14,
    "Doctorate": 15,
    "Prof-school": 16
    }
    data['gender'] = data['gender'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x == 'Male' else 0)
    data['income'] = data['income'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x == '>50K' else 0)
    data['native-country'] = data['native-country'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x == 'United-States' else 0)
    data['education'] = data['education'].apply(lambda x: education_levels[x])

    categorical_vars = ['workclass', 'marital-status', 'occupation', 'relationship', 'race']
    encoder = OneHotEncoder()
    cat_encoded = encoder.fit_transform(data[categorical_vars])

    cat_encoded_array = cat_encoded.toarray()
    cat_encoded_df = pd.DataFrame(cat_encoded_array, columns=encoder.get_feature_names_out(categorical_vars))
    data.drop(columns=categorical_vars, inplace=True)
    data = pd.concat([data, cat_encoded_df], axis=1)
    return data
   
def predict_fn(model, df):
    df.loc[:, df.dtypes == 'object'] =\
        df.select_dtypes(['object'])\
        .apply(lambda x: x.astype('category'))
    return model.predict_proba(df)[:, 1]

sample = np.random.choice(len(X_test), 3)

for idx in sample:
    prediction = explainer.predict(X.iloc[[idx]])
    print(prediction)
    for seed in range(3):
        random.seed(seed)

        exp = explainer.predict_surrogate(X.iloc[idx])
        fig = exp.plot(return_figure=True)
        plt.title(f'Explanation for observation with id {X.index[idx]}, predicition={prediction}, seed={seed}')
